---
description: Two-way parity check between Java CLI output and Node.js API output. Use after any change to nodejs-api/ to verify outputs still match.
alwaysApply: false
---

Run a two-way parity check for the order input I specify.

Steps:
1. Run Java CLI:
   java -jar java-order-system/target/order-processing-system-1.0.0-jar-with-dependencies.jar [INPUT_FILE]

2. Call Node.js API:
   curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/orders \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @[INPUT_FILE]

Compare these fields across both (exclude processedAt):
  status, grandTotal, subtotal, totalTax, promoDiscount, shippingCost,
  promoCode, fraudFlags[].flag, fraudFlags[].severity, errors[]

If all match: print "✅ PARITY VERIFIED"
If any differ: print the field name, expected value (CLI), actual value (Node API), and likely cause based on ai-context/BUSINESS_RULES.md.

Run for all 5 files in java-order-system/test-inputs/ unless I specify one file.
